% Lore local da geracao 4
% Formato: pokemon_lore(ID, Texto).
:- multifile pokemon_lore/2.
pokemon_lore(387, 'The shell on its back is made of soil. On a very healthy TURTWIG, the shell should feel moist.').
pokemon_lore(388, 'It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.').
pokemon_lore(389, 'Some Pokémon are born on a TORTERRA’s back and spend their entire life there.').
pokemon_lore(390, 'It is very agile. Before going to sleep, it extinguishes the flame on its tail to prevent fires.').
pokemon_lore(391, 'It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.').
pokemon_lore(392, 'It uses unique fighting moves with fire on its hands and feet. It will take on any opponent.').
pokemon_lore(393, 'A poor walker, it often falls down. However, its strong pride makes it puff up its chest without a care.').
pokemon_lore(394, 'Because every PRINPLUP considers itself to be the most important, they can never form a group.').
pokemon_lore(395, 'If anyone were to hurt its pride, it would slash them with wings that can cleave through an ice floe.').
pokemon_lore(396, 'Because they are weak individually, they form groups. However, they bicker if the group grows too big.').
pokemon_lore(397, 'Recognizing their own weakness, they always live in a group. When alone, a STARAVIA cries noisily.').
pokemon_lore(398, 'It never stops attacking even if it is injured. It fusses over the shape of its comb.').
pokemon_lore(399, 'A comparison revealed that BIDOOF’s front teeth grow at the same rate as RATTATA’s.').
pokemon_lore(400, 'A river dammed by BIBAREL will never overflow its banks, which is appreciated by people nearby.').
pokemon_lore(401, 'Its legs are short. Whenever it stumbles, its stiff antennae clack with a xylophone-like sound.').
pokemon_lore(402, 'There is a village that hosts a contest based on the amazingly variable cries of this Pokémon.').
pokemon_lore(403, 'The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.').
pokemon_lore(404, 'Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.').
pokemon_lore(405, 'It can see clearly through walls to track down its prey and seek its lost young.').
pokemon_lore(406, 'Sensitive to changing temperature, the bud is said to bloom when it feels the sun’s warm touch.').
pokemon_lore(407, 'Each of its hands contains different toxins, but both hands can jab with near-fatal power.').
pokemon_lore(408, 'A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million years ago, it would snap obstructing trees with head butts.').
pokemon_lore(409, 'If two were to smash their heads together, their foot-thick skulls would keep them from fainting.').
pokemon_lore(410, 'It is outstandingly armored. As a result, it can eat grass and berries without having to fight.').
pokemon_lore(411, 'When they lined up side by side, no foe could break through. They shielded their young in that way.').
pokemon_lore(412, 'Even if it is born where there are no cocooning materials, it somehow always ends up with a cloak.').
pokemon_lore(413, 'When evolving, its body takes in surrounding materials. As a result, there are many body variations.').
pokemon_lore(414, 'While it loves floral honey, it won’t gather any itself. Instead, it plots to steal some from COMBEE.').
pokemon_lore(415, 'The trio is together from birth. It constantly gathers honey from flowers to please VESPIQUEN.').
pokemon_lore(416, 'It releases various pheromones to make the grubs in its body do its bidding while fighting foes.').
pokemon_lore(417, 'A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.').
pokemon_lore(418, 'It spins its two tails like a screw to propel itself through water. The tails also slice clinging seaweed.').
pokemon_lore(419, 'It is a common sight around fishing ports. It is known to rescue people and carry off prey.').
pokemon_lore(420, 'The small ball is not only filled with nutrients, it is also tasty. STARLY try to peck it off.').
pokemon_lore(421, 'If it senses strong sunlight, it opens its folded petals to absorb the sun’s rays with its whole body.').
pokemon_lore(422, 'Beware of pushing strongly on its squishy body, as it makes a mysterious purple fluid ooze out.').
pokemon_lore(423, 'Long ago, its entire back was shielded with a sturdy shell. There are traces of it left in its cells.').
pokemon_lore(424, 'Split into two, the tails are so adept at handling and doing things, AMBIPOM rarely uses its hands.').
pokemon_lore(425, 'Because of the way it floats aimlessly, an old folktale calls it a “Signpost for Wandering Spirits.”').
pokemon_lore(426, 'At dusk, swarms of them are carried aloft on winds. When noticed, they suddenly vanish.').
pokemon_lore(427, 'Its ears are always rolled up. They can be forcefully extended to shatter even a large boulder.').
pokemon_lore(428, 'The ears appear to be delicate. If they are touched roughly, it kicks with its graceful legs.').
pokemon_lore(429, 'Its cry sounds like an incantation. It is said the cry may rarely be imbued with happiness-giving power.').
pokemon_lore(430, 'If one utters a deep cry, many MURKROW gather quickly. For this, it is called “Summoner of Night.”').
pokemon_lore(431, 'It hides its spiteful tendency of hooking its claws into the nose of its Trainer if it isn’t fed.').
pokemon_lore(432, 'It binds its body with its tails to make itself look bigger. If it locks eyes, it will glare ceaselessly.').
pokemon_lore(433, 'There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops, the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.').
pokemon_lore(434, 'It sprays a foul fluid from its rear. Its stench spreads over a mile radius, driving Pokémon away.').
pokemon_lore(435, 'It attacks by spraying a horribly smelly fluid from the tip of its tail. Attacks from above confound it.').
pokemon_lore(436, 'There are researchers who believe this Pokémon reflected like a mirror in the distant past.').
pokemon_lore(437, 'It brought rains by opening portals to another world. It was revered as a bringer of plentiful harvests.').
pokemon_lore(438, 'It prefers an arid atmosphere. It leaks water that looks like tears when adjusting its moisture level.').
pokemon_lore(439, 'It mimics the expressions and motions of those it sees to understand the feelings of others.').
pokemon_lore(440, 'It likes to carry around a small rock. It may wander around others’ feet and cause them to stumble.').
pokemon_lore(441, 'Its tongue is just like a human’s. As a result, it can cleverly mimic human speech.').
pokemon_lore(442, 'Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.').
pokemon_lore(443, 'It attacks using its huge mouth. While its attacks are powerful, it hurts itself out of clumsiness, too.').
pokemon_lore(444, 'It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.').
pokemon_lore(445, 'It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.').
pokemon_lore(446, 'In its desperation to gulp down food, it forgets about the food it has hidden under its fur.').
pokemon_lore(447, 'It has the peculiar power of being able to see emotions such as joy and rage in the form of waves.').
pokemon_lore(448, 'A well-trained one can sense auras to identify and take in the feelings of creatures over half a mile away.').
pokemon_lore(449, 'It shuts its nostrils tight then travels through sand as if walking. They form colonies of around ten.').
pokemon_lore(450, 'It is surprisingly quick to anger. It holds its mouth agape as a display of its strength.').
pokemon_lore(451, 'As soon as the tail claws close, its needle tips secrete poison. It can survive a year without food.').
pokemon_lore(452, 'Possessing a sturdy build, it takes pride in its strength, taking down foes without using toxins.').
pokemon_lore(453, 'It rarely fights fairly, but that is strictly to ensure survival. It is popular as a mascot.').
pokemon_lore(454, 'It has a poison sac at its throat. When it croaks, the stored poison is churned for greater potency.').
pokemon_lore(455, 'It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet- smelling drool and gulps them down.').
pokemon_lore(456, 'The line running down its side can store sunlight. It shines vividly at night.').
pokemon_lore(457, 'It crawls along the seafloor using its long front fins like legs. It competes for food with LANTURN.').
pokemon_lore(458, 'People organize tours to see this Pokémon frolic and skim the tops of waves with REMORAID.').
pokemon_lore(459, 'Seemingly curious about people, they gather around footsteps they find on snowy mountains.').
pokemon_lore(460, 'They appear when the snow flowers bloom. When the petals fall, they retreat to places unknown again.').
pokemon_lore(461, 'Evolution made it even more devious. It communicates by clawing signs in boulders.').
pokemon_lore(462, 'A group tried to use scientific means to make MAGNEZONE evolve, but their efforts ended in failure.').
pokemon_lore(463, 'The long tongue is always soggy with slobber. The saliva contains a solvent that causes numbness.').
pokemon_lore(464, 'It can launch a rock held in its hand like a missile by tightening then expanding muscles instantly.').
pokemon_lore(465, 'Its arms are made of plants that bind themselves to things. They grow back right away if cut.').
pokemon_lore(466, 'Heedless of enemy attacks, it closes in, shoves its tails onto the foe, then looses high voltage.').
pokemon_lore(467, 'When launching 3,600 degrees F fireballs, its body takes on a whitish hue from the intense heat.').
pokemon_lore(468, 'It shares many blessings with people who respect one another’s rights and avoid needless strife.').
pokemon_lore(469, 'Its jaw power is incredible. It is adept at biting apart foes while flying by at high speed.').
pokemon_lore(470, 'It basically does not fight. With cells similar to those of plants, it can perform photosynthesis.').
pokemon_lore(471, 'By controlling its body heat, it can freeze the atmosphere around it to make a diamond-dust flurry.').
pokemon_lore(472, 'If it succeeds in catching even a faint breeze properly, it can circle the globe without flapping once.').
pokemon_lore(473, 'A frozen one was dug up from soil dating back 10,000 years. It woke up to much amazement.').
pokemon_lore(474, 'Its programming was modified to enable work in alien dimensions. It did not work as planned.').
pokemon_lore(475, 'When trying to protect someone, it extends its elbows as if they were swords and fights savagely.').
pokemon_lore(476, 'It freely controls three small units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.').
pokemon_lore(477, 'It is said to take lost spirits into its pliant body and guide them home.').
pokemon_lore(478, 'It freezes prey by blowing its -58 degrees F breath. It is said to then secretly display its prey.').
pokemon_lore(479, 'Its electric-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.').
pokemon_lore(480, 'When UXIE flew, people gained the ability to solve problems. It was the birth of knowledge.').
pokemon_lore(481, 'When MESPRIT flew, people learned the joy and sadness of living. It was the birth of emotions.').
pokemon_lore(482, 'When AZELF flew, people gained the determination to do things. It was the birth of willpower.').
pokemon_lore(483, 'A legendary Pokémon of Sinnoh. It is said that time flows when DIALGA’s heart beats.').
pokemon_lore(484, 'A legendary Pokémon of Sinnoh. It is said that space becomes more stable with PALKIA’s every breath.').
pokemon_lore(485, 'Its body is made of rugged steel. However, it is partially melted in spots because of its own heat.').
pokemon_lore(486, 'It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.').
pokemon_lore(487, 'It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.').
pokemon_lore(488, 'On nights around the quarter moon, the aurora from its tail extends and undulates beautifully.').
pokemon_lore(489, 'It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.').
pokemon_lore(490, 'It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.').
pokemon_lore(491, 'To protect itself, it afflicts those around it with nightmares. However, it means no harm.').
pokemon_lore(492, 'The flowers all over its body burst into bloom if it is lovingly hugged and senses gratitude.').
pokemon_lore(493, 'It is said to have emerged from an egg in a place where there was nothing, then shaped the world.').
